body:
@kasper3 this project has evolved and created a dependency on PSCore6 itself to build the entire project.  I believe you really need to just build two things on any new platform that .Net Core supports:

- libpsl-native is cmake based and you just need to perform the equivalent of [these steps in build.psm1](https://github.com/PowerShell/PowerShell/blob/dcba3c486e77b9fbceaf9504426d067df8898b70/build.psm1#L368)
- powershell itself you should be able to initially get away with `dotnet restore`, `dotnet publish` if the dotnet SDK is available
